(0) 0% of the test frames are marked discard eligible (25) 25% of the test frames are marked discard eligible (50) 50% of the test frames are marked discard eligible (75) 75% of the test frames are marked discard eligible (100) 100% of the test frames are marked discard eligible

tfrapDiagVBERTTestPeriod.name: tfrapDiagVBERTTestPeriod
tfrapDiagVBERTTestPeriod.description: Specifies the duration of a VBERT test. Note that VBERT is subjected to the unit's Loopback Timer and will be terminated by whichever timer expires first. (10-1440): VBERT time duration in seconds

tfrapIntfDteMode.name: tfrapIntfDteMode
tfrapIntfDteMode.description: Status of allocation of T1 bandwidth to the DTE port data. (1) no connections - indicates the DTE port has no connections to the WAN. (2) Active - indicates DTE data rate has been assigned T1 DS0s and is in a normal data mode. (3) Test - indicates DTE data rate has been assigned T1 DS0s but is in a diagnostic condition.

tfrapIntfDteRts.name: tfrapIntfDteRts
tfrapIntfDteRts.description: Status of the Request to Send (RTS) signal from the DTE port. (1) RTS Active (2) RTS Inactive

tfrapIntfDteDtr.name: tfrapIntfDteDtr
tfrapIntfDteDtr.description: Status of the Data Terminal Ready (DTR) signal from the DTE port. (1) DTR Active (2) DTR Inactive

tfrapIntfT1Mode.name: tfrapIntfT1Mode
tfrapIntfT1Mode.description: Status of allocation of T1 bandwidth to the DTE port data. (1) no connections - indicates the DTE port has no connections to the WAN. (2) Active - indicates DTE data rate has been assigned T1 DS0s and is in a normal data mode. (3) Test - indicates DTE data rate has been assigned T1 DS0s but is in a diagnostic condition.

tfrapIntfT1Status.name: tfrapIntfT1Status
tfrapIntfT1Status.description: Status of the signal received from the WAN (1) In Sync - unit has detected a properly framed T1 signal and is not experiencing any error conditions. (2) In Sync with Errors - unit has detected a properly framed T1 signal but is experiencing some error conditions. Refer to T1 current performance results for details. (3) Signal Detected without Frame Sync - while a signal is present from the WAN it does not contain the framing pattern defined for this unit. This could be either incorrectly configured T1 Frame type or the presence of an alarm condition on the WAN. (4) No Carrier - there is no signal detected from the WAN. (5) Not Applicable.

tfrapIntfT1Alarms.name: tfrapIntfT1Alarms
tfrapIntfT1Alarms.description: Alarms present at the T1 port. (1) No alarm conditions present. (2) Red Alarm Declared - Unit has experienced loss of frame synchronization with the signal received from the WAN for an extended time and is reporting an alarm condition that severely impairs normal operation. During this Red Alarm condition the unit will transmit Yellow alarm back to the WAN. If this condition persists consult your service provider. (3) Yellow ALarm Detected - Unit is receiving a yellow alarm indication from the wide area network. Detection of yellow alarm implies that the attached device is in a red alarm conditon. Red alarm is declared due to the extended absence of a properly framed signal. If this condition persists consult your service provider. (4) Unframe All Ones Detected - Unit is receiving unframed all ones from the wide area network (AIS, blue alarm). Detection of AIS implies that the attached device is reporting an alarm condition from an upstream device. If this condition persists consult your service provider.

tfrapIntfDteDcd.name: tfrapIntfDteDcd
tfrapIntfDteDcd.description: Status of the Data Carrier Detect (DCD) signal driven by this unit towards the DTE port (1) DCD Active (2) DCD Inactive

tfrapIntfDteDsr.name: tfrapIntfDteDsr
tfrapIntfDteDsr.description: Status of the Data Set Ready (DSR) signal driven by this unit towards the DTE port. (1) DSR Active (2) DSR Inactive

tfrapIntfDteCts.name: tfrapIntfDteCts
tfrapIntfDteCts.description: Status of the Clear to Send (CTS) signal driven by this unit towards the DTE port (1) CTS Active (2) CTS Inactive

tfrapStatusDteModeLED.name: tfrapStatusDteModeLED
tfrapStatusDteModeLED.description: Status of the DTE Mode LED. (1) DTE Mode LED off: Missing control signals (2) DTE Mode LED green: Normal (3) DTE Mode LED yellow: Test Mode

tfrapStatusDteStatusLED.name: tfrapStatusDteStatusLED
tfrapStatusDteStatusLED.description: Status of the DTE Status LED. (1) DTE Status LED off: no connections to WAN (2) DTE Status LED green: normal

tfrapStatusDteTxLED.name: tfrapStatusDteTxLED
tfrapStatusDteTxLED.description: Status of the DTE Tx Data LED. In Frame Relay mode, this LED is ON (green) when the DTE is not sending HDLC Flags and is OFF when HDLC flags are being transmit. In CBO mode, the LED is ON (green) for a SPACE and OFF for a MARK. (1) DTE Transmit LED OFF: inactive (HDLC flags or CBO marks) (2) DTE Transmit LED ON: active (HDLC frames or CBO spaces)

tfrapStatusDteRxLED.name: tfrapStatusDteRxLED
tfrapStatusDteRxLED.description: Status of the DTE Rx Data LED. In Frame Relay mode, this LED is ON (green) when the WAN is receiving HDLC Flags and is OFF when HDLC flags are being received. In CBO mode, the LED is ON (green) for a SPACE and OFF for a MARK. (1) DTE Receive LED OFF: inactive (HDLC flags or CBO marks) (2) DTE Receive LED ON: active (HDLC frames or CBO spaces)

tfrapStatusT1ModeLED.name: tfrapStatusT1ModeLED
tfrapStatusT1ModeLED.description: Status of the WAN Mode LED. (1) WAN Mode LED is green: normal data mode (2) WAN Mode LED is yellow: test mode

tfrapStatusT1StatusLED.name: tfrapStatusT1StatusLED
tfrapStatusT1StatusLED.description: Status of the WAN Status LED. (1) Off - no signal detected from WAN. (2) Green - framed signal detected with no errors (normal operation) (3) Yellow - remote alarm condition detected (yellow or AIS alarms) (4) Red - unit has declared Red Alarm due to the presence of an improperly framed signal from the WAN. (5) Blinking Red and Off - unit has declared Red Alarm due to the absence of a signal from the WAN. (6) Blinking Green and Red - unit is receiving a properly framed signal from the WAN but has detected a transient error condition. Possible Line Code Violations or ESF CRC errors indicating errored data bits. (7) Blinking Red and Yellow - unit is receiving an unframed all ones (AIS) from the WAN. This is indicative of an upstream alarm condition on the WAN.

tfrapStatusAllLEDs.name: tfrapStatusAllLEDs
tfrapStatusAllLEDs.description: Status of all six TFRAP LEDs, encoded in a string. 'F' off '5' green '0' yellow 'A' red '7' blinking green and off '3' blinking yellow and off 'B' blinking red and off '4' blinking green and yellow '6' blinking green and red '8' blinking yellow and red Positionally, the 6 letters are DTE Mode, DTE status, Dte Tx, Dte Rx, T1 Mode, and T1 Status. For example, '555556' would mean: DTE in normal mode, active status, transmitting and receiving and T1 normal with transient errors.

tfrapVnipTopologyTable.name: tfrapVnipTopologyTable
tfrapVnipTopologyTable.description: VNIP topology is a feature that, for each interface, maps all compatible VNIP peers, their DLCI value, ip address and relative location. The topology is a fundamental prerequisite to applying the VNIP feature set which includes PVC-based delay measurement, diagnostics, and congestion monitoring. With VNIP enabled on an interface the unit will attempt to locate VNIP peers out that port. As peers are discovered and logged the unit will report the topology it has learned on its opposite interface. If VNIP is inactive on one interface it will not engage in any VNIP dialog; however it will continue to listen for topology messages on the inactive interface and will reflect these messages out the opposite interface if VNIP is enabled. With VNIP inactive on both interfaces the unit will transparently pass all VNIP messages. The topology database includes the interface, local DLCI value, remote peer DLCI value, remote peer ip address, and the number of VNIP hops in between. This table also reports the status of other VNIP features as well.

tfrapVnipTopologyEntry.name: tfrapVnipTopologyEntry
tfrapVnipTopologyEntry.description: The DLCI, IP address, and number of hops for a particular node, discovered via VNIP off of an interface. The entry may also have transit delay measurements and VBERT diagnostic status to report as well.

tfrapVnipTopologyInterface.name: tfrapVnipTopologyInterface
tfrapVnipTopologyInterface.description: The interface off of which the peer was discovered. Topology is discovered by sending VNIP messages out each interface. Units discovered via a particular interface are kept in a list associated with that interface. (1) VNIP peers and status out DTE interface (2) VNIP peers and status out WAN interface

tfrapVnipTopologyIndex.name: tfrapVnipTopologyIndex
tfrapVnipTopologyIndex.description: The number of this discovered peer in the list of nodes for this interface. For each interface, the nodes are numbered 1 through n. This index is required when disabling or enabling VBERT/VLOOP to a particular peer.

tfrapVnipTopologyDlci.name: tfrapVnipTopologyDlci
tfrapVnipTopologyDlci.description: The DLCI of the discovered neighboring peer. This may be different from the local DLCI.

tfrapVnipTopologyIpAddr.name: tfrapVnipTopologyIpAddr
tfrapVnipTopologyIpAddr.description: The IP address for the discovered peer.

tfrapVnipTopologyNumHops.name: tfrapVnipTopologyNumHops
tfrapVnipTopologyNumHops.description: The discovered peer is this number of hops away. Each hop is a VNIP peer.

tfrapVnipTopologyLocalDlci.name: tfrapVnipTopologyLocalDlci
tfrapVnipTopologyLocalDlci.description: The DLCI from this unit over which the remote peer was discovered.

tfrapVnipTopoTDNumSamples.name: tfrapVnipTopoTDNumSamples
tfrapVnipTopoTDNumSamples.description: The number of transit delay samples collected.

tfrapVnipTopoTDAvgDelay.name: tfrapVnipTopoTDAvgDelay
tfrapVnipTopoTDAvgDelay.description: The average transit delay between this unit and the remote peer (in milliseconds).

tfrapVnipTopoTDMaxDelay.name: tfrapVnipTopoTDMaxDelay
tfrapVnipTopoTDMaxDelay.description: The maximum transit delay between this node and the remote peer (in milliseconds).

tfrapVnipTopoTDMinDelay.name: tfrapVnipTopoTDMinDelay
tfrapVnipTopoTDMinDelay.description: The minimum transit delay between this node and the remote peer (in milliseconds).

tfrapVnipTopoTDLastDelay.name: tfrapVnipTopoTDLastDelay
tfrapVnipTopoTDLastDelay.description: The most recent transit delay measured between this node and the remote peer (in milliseconds).

tfrapVnipTopoVLOOPStatus.name: tfrapVnipTopoVLOOPStatus
tfrapVnipTopoVLOOPStatus.description: This selection displays the status of the VNIP PVC Loopback for this entry. This loopback is initiated by the remote node through the VLOOP utility, causing this node to loop data back to the remote node. (1) Virtual Loopback path present on this PVC due to command received from remote unit. All data received on this DLCI will be looped back out the same interface. (2) No active VLOOP test on this

tfrapVnipTopoVBERTStatus.name: tfrapVnipTopoVBERTStatus
tfrapVnipTopoVBERTStatus.description: Displays the current status of the VBERT/VLOOP test. (1) Off: no test has run or the entry has been cleared (2) Testing: the entry is generating VBERT test frames (3) Test Failed: the request for a test on this entry failed (4) Test Completed: a test has run and is finished results are complete (5) In Test: the entry is on the receiving end of VBERT packets

tfrapVnipTopoVBertTxDESetFrames.name: tfrapVnipTopoVBertTxDESetFrames
tfrapVnipTopoVBertTxDESetFrames.description: Displays the number of Frames transmitted during VBERT Test that had the Discard Eligibility indicator bit set.

tfrapVnipTopoVBertRxDESetFrames.name: tfrapVnipTopoVBertRxDESetFrames
tfrapVnipTopoVBertRxDESetFrames.description: Displays the number of Frames received during VBERT Test that had the Discard Eligibility indicator bit set.

tfrapVnipTopoVBertTxDEClrFrames.name: tfrapVnipTopoVBertTxDEClrFrames
tfrapVnipTopoVBertTxDEClrFrames.description: Displays the number of Frames transmitted during VBERT Test that had the Discard Eligibility indicator bit cleared.

tfrapVnipTopoVBertRxDEClrFrames.name: tfrapVnipTopoVBertRxDEClrFrames
tfrapVnipTopoVBertRxDEClrFrames.description: Displays the number of Frames received during VBERT Test that had the Discard Eligibility indicator bit cleared.

tfrapVnipTopoVBertTransitDelayMax.name: tfrapVnipTopoVBertTransitDelayMax
tfrapVnipTopoVBertTransitDelayMax.description: The maximum transit delay between this node and the remote peer during the VBERT test. This delay measurement will include internal device latencies. This result may differ from the VNIP transit delay measurement which accounts for internal latencies.

tfrapVnipTopoVBertTransitDelayAvg.name: tfrapVnipTopoVBertTransitDelayAvg
tfrapVnipTopoVBertTransitDelayAvg.description: The average transit delay between this node and the remote peer during the VBERT test. This delay measurement will include internal device latencies. This result may differ from the VNIP transit delay measurement which accounts for internal latencies

tfrapVnipTopoVBertTimeElapse.name: tfrapVnipTopoVBertTimeElapse
tfrapVnipTopoVBertTimeElapse.description: Elapsed time since VBERT/VLOOP test was started or cleared (in seconds).

tfrapVnipTopoVBertPerUtilCIR.name: tfrapVnipTopoVBertPerUtilCIR
tfrapVnipTopoVBertPerUtilCIR.description: The calculated percent of CIR utilization during a VBERT test, this value is only valid after a test is complete not during.

tfrapVnipTopoVBertPerUtilEIR.name: tfrapVnipTopoVBertPerUtilEIR
tfrapVnipTopoVBertPerUtilEIR.description: The calculated percent of EIR utilization during a VBERT test, this value is only valid after a test is complete not during.

tfrapVnipTransitDelayClear.name: tfrapVnipTransitDelayClear
tfrapVnipTransitDelayClear.description: Allows the user to clear all the VNIP Transit Delay data collected in the VNIP topology database. (1) Clear entire Transit Delay results database

tfrapLmiSourcing.name: tfrapLmiSourcing
tfrapLmiSourcing.description: If configured for Frame Relay with a non-zero LMI inactivity timer the unit will monitor the status of LMI and, if proper messaging is not detected, will attempt to emulate either Frame Relay DTE or DCE devices in attempt to restore LMI to any attached equipment and provide managed access for diagnostic purposes. Typically frads/routers are Frame Relay DTE while switches are Frame Relay DCE but this model may vary. In the absence of full-duplex LMI, the unit will cycle through various states in attempt to adapt to an LMI partner. The unit will try each state for the duration of the LMI Inactivity timer and then advance to the next one if satisfactory handshaking is not established. While in any of these states if full-duplex LMI handshaking does appear, the unit will immediately revert to the passthrough state. (1) initializing (2) Passthrough: not sourcing any LMI messages. (3) Status Enquiries out DTE interface: unit is emulating a Frame Relay DTE device out the its (physical) DTE interface. (4) Status Enquiries out WAN interface: unit is emulating a Frame Relay DTE device out the its WAN interface. (5) Status Responses out the DTE interface: unit is emulating a Frame Relay DCE device out the its (physical) DTE interface (provisioning the single default management DLCI). (6) Status Responses out the WAN interface: unit is emulating a Frame Relay DCE device out the its WAN interface (provisioning the single default management DLCI). (7) Disabled - LMI Inactivity timer is zero or unit not configured for a Frame Relay application. (8) Status Responses out both DTE and WAN interfaces: unit is configured for Fixed DCE mode of management and emulates a Frame Relay DCE independently on both ports (provisioning the single default management DLCI).

tfrapVBertClear.name: tfrapVBertClear
tfrapVBertClear.description: Allows the user to clear all the VBERT data collected in the VNIP topology database as long as the entry is not in a test status. (1) Clear all VBERT/VLOOP status information

tfrapStatusMgmtChannel.name: tfrapStatusMgmtChannel
tfrapStatusMgmtChannel.description: This is the method in which the unit is configured for SNMP management access. (1) None: SNMP management disabled (2) SLIP: out-of-band management via asynchronous Serial Line IP (3) Private DLCI: in-band management using a private DLCI that is dedicated solely to this unit's management. (4) Piggyback DLCI: in-band management using any DLCI optionally multiplexing both management and user data.

tfrapStatusMgmtInterface.name: tfrapStatusMgmtInterface
tfrapStatusMgmtInterface.description: This is the port(s) on which the management traffic will appear. (1) Async Maintenance(Comm)/Console port - SLIP mode (2) Local DTE interface: unit is configured for Private Local DLCI mode (3) Remote WAN Interface: unit is confiogured for Private Remote DLCI mode (4) DTE and WAN Interfaces: unit is configured for either Piggyback Bidirectional mode.

tfrapStatusMgmtInterfaceStatus.name: tfrapStatusMgmtInterfaceStatus
tfrapStatusMgmtInterfaceStatus.description: This is the status of the port(s) on which the management traffic will appear. (1) Active: port or DLCI is configured and status is okay (2) Inactive: port or DLCI is declared out of service (3) Alarm: port or DLCI is experiencing an alarm condition that may interefere with management access

tfrapStatusMgmtDefaultDLCINo.name: tfrapStatusMgmtDefaultDLCINo
tfrapStatusMgmtDefaultDLCINo.description: This is the DLCI for the PVC that is defined for the Management port. All traffic using this DLCI in the Frame Replay packet will be destined for the InBand Management task.

tfrapStatusMgmtDefaultDLCIStatus.name: tfrapStatusMgmtDefaultDLCIStatus
tfrapStatusMgmtDefaultDLCIStatus.description: This is the status of the default management DLCI. (1) not applicable: SLIP mode or management is disabled (2) DLCI Active: default DLCI is active in the LMI full status response. (3) DLCI Inactive: default DLCI is not active in the LMI full status response.

tfrapStatusLmiAutosense.name: tfrapStatusLmiAutosense
tfrapStatusLmiAutosense.description: This indicates the current status of LMI Auto Sensing if it's enabled. (1) Disabled: LMI is configured as Type 1, Annex-D, or Annex-A (2) Searching: unit is attempting to determine the LMI type of the attached equipment by issuing LMI messages of each LMI type and searching for responses. (3) Learned Annex-D: unit has successfully detected Annex-D LMI (ANSI T1.617 Annex D) (4) Learned Annex-A: unit has successfully detected Annex-A LMI (ITU/CCITT Q.933 Annex A) (5) Learned Type 1: unit has successfully detected Type 1 LMI (Cisco, Group of four, LMI)

tfrapPerfT1CurrentTable.name: tfrapPerfT1CurrentTable
tfrapPerfT1CurrentTable.description: The T1 physical layer performance numbers for the current 15 minute interval. These are defined and accumulated per ANSI specification T1.403 and AT&T publication 54016. Depending upon the configured T1 Framing mode, these results may be retrieved via ESF facility data link by service personnel.

tfrapT1CurrentEntry.name: tfrapT1CurrentEntry
tfrapT1CurrentEntry.description: An entry in the T1 Current Perf table. This table is structured for devices to support multiple T1 interfaces.

tfrapT1CurrentIndex.name: tfrapT1CurrentIndex
tfrapT1CurrentIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the T1 interface to which this entry is applicable. There's only one T1 on this unit so the index will always be 1.

tfrapT1CurrentCrc6Events.name: tfrapT1CurrentCrc6Events
tfrapT1CurrentCrc6Events.description: Count of CRC errors detected on an ESF framed circuit. In ESF framing a CRC is generated at the source, based upon the composite data. A CRC error indicates the presence of at least one bit error in an ESF superframe. This field is a free-running accumulation of CRC errors and IS NOT reset when the current 15 minute interval expires. It can be reset with the performance command tfrapT1PerfClearEvents. Not applicable if D4/SF framing is selcted.

tfrapT1CurrentOofEvents.name: tfrapT1CurrentOofEvents
tfrapT1CurrentOofEvents.description: Count of Out-of-Frame events on a T1 circuit. An out-of- frame event occurs when the frame synchronization criteria is lost and a resynchronization must occur. Data is interrupted during frame resynchronization. This field is a free-running accumulation of OOF transitions and IS NOT reset when the current 15 minute interval expires. It can be reset with the performance command tfrapT1PerfClearEvents.

tfrapT1CurrentESs.name: tfrapT1CurrentESs
tfrapT1CurrentESs.description: The number of Errored Seconds, encountered by a T1 interface in the current 15 minute inter- val. An errored second is a one-second interval with CRC errors or a loss of frame sync occurred.

tfrapT1CurrentSESs.name: tfrapT1CurrentSESs
tfrapT1CurrentSESs.description: The number of Severely Errored Seconds encountered by a t1 interface in the current 15 minute interval. A severely errored second is a one second interval with more than 320 CRC errors or one or more frame sync losses.

tfrapT1CurrentSEFSs.name: tfrapT1CurrentSEFSs
tfrapT1CurrentSEFSs.description: The number of Severely Errored Framing Seconds encountered by a t1 interface in the current 15 minute interval. A SEFS is a one second interval with one or more frame sync losses.

tfrapT1CurrentUASs.name: tfrapT1CurrentUASs
tfrapT1CurrentUASs.description: The number of Unavailable Seconds encountered by a t1 interface in the current 15 minute in- terval. A UAS is a one second interval during which the received signal is classified as 'unavailable due to excessive errors'. A signal is unavailable after receiving ten consective severely errored seconds and stays unavailable until ten seconds without a severely errored second occur.

tfrapT1CurrentCSSs.name: tfrapT1CurrentCSSs
tfrapT1CurrentCSSs.description: The number of Controlled Slip Seconds encoun- tered by a t1 interface in the current 15 minute interval. A controlled slip is the replication or deletion of a T1 frame at the receiver. These events often indicate a T1 network timing problem.

tfrapT1CurrentBESs.name: tfrapT1CurrentBESs
tfrapT1CurrentBESs.description: The number of Bursty Errored Seconds (BESs) encountered by a DS1 interface in the current 15 minute interval. A BES is a one second interval with more than one and less than 320 CRC errors.

tfrapT1CurrentLCVs.name: tfrapT1CurrentLCVs
tfrapT1CurrentLCVs.description: The number of Line Code Violations (LCVs) en- countered by a DS1 interface in the current 15 minute interval. LCVs are non-B8ZS related violations of the alternate mark inversion protocol. An excessive count usually indicates a B8ZS/AMI configuration mismatch in the T1 network.

tfrapPerfT1IntervalTable.name: tfrapPerfT1IntervalTable
tfrapPerfT1IntervalTable.description: The DS1 Interval table. A history of physical layer performance results are maintained and represented as 96 15-minute intervals. These are defined and accumulated per ANSI specification T1.403 and AT&T publication 54016. Depending upon the configured T1 Framing mode, these results may be retrieved via ESF facility data link by service personnel

tfrapT1IntervalEntry.name: tfrapT1IntervalEntry
tfrapT1IntervalEntry.description: An entry in the DS1 Interval table which includes physical layer statistics for each of the prior 96 15-minute intervals.

tfrapT1IntervalIndex.name: tfrapT1IntervalIndex
tfrapT1IntervalIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the t1 interface to which this entry is applicable. There is only one T1 on this unit so this index will be 1.

tfrapT1IntervalNumber.name: tfrapT1IntervalNumber
tfrapT1IntervalNumber.description: A number between 1 and 96, where 96 is the most recently completed 15 minute interval and 1 occurred 24 hours ago (assuming that all 96 intervals are valid).

tfrapT1IntervalESs.name: tfrapT1IntervalESs
tfrapT1IntervalESs.description: The number of Errored Seconds encountered by a t1 interface in one of the previous 96, indi- vidual 15 minute, intervals. An errored second is a one-second interval with CRC errors or a loss of frame sync occurred.

tfrapT1IntervalSESs.name: tfrapT1IntervalSESs
tfrapT1IntervalSESs.description: The number of Severely Errored Seconds encoun- tered by a t1 interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals. A severely errored second is a one second interval with more than 320 CRC errors or one or more frame sync losses.

tfrapT1IntervalSEFSs.name: tfrapT1IntervalSEFSs
tfrapT1IntervalSEFSs.description: The number of Severely Errored Framing Seconds encountered by a t1 interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals. A SEFS is a one second interval with one or more frame sync losses.

tfrapT1IntervalUASs.name: tfrapT1IntervalUASs
tfrapT1IntervalUASs.description: The number of Unavailable Seconds encountered by a t1 interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals. A UAS is a one second interval during which the received signal is classified as 'unavailable due to excessive errors'. A signal is unavailable after receiving ten consective severely errored seconds and stays unavailable until ten seconds without a severely errored second occur.

tfrapT1IntervalCSSs.name: tfrapT1IntervalCSSs
tfrapT1IntervalCSSs.description: The number of Controlled Slip Seconds encoun- tered by a t1 interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals. A controlled slip is the replication or deletion of a T1 frame at the receiver. These events often indicate a T1 network timing problem.

tfrapT1IntervalBESs.name: tfrapT1IntervalBESs
tfrapT1IntervalBESs.description: The number of Bursty Errored Seconds (BESs) encountered by a t1 interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals. A BES is a one second interval with more than one and less than 320 CRC errors.

tfrapT1IntervalLCVs.name: tfrapT1IntervalLCVs
tfrapT1IntervalLCVs.description: The number of Line Code Violations (LCVs) en- countered by a DS1 interface in the current 15 minute interval. LCVs are non-B8ZS related violations of the alternate mark inversion protocol. An excessive count usually indicates a B8ZS/AMI configuration mismatch in the T1 network.

tfrapPerfT1TotalTable.name: tfrapPerfT1TotalTable
tfrapPerfT1TotalTable.description: The T1 Total table cumulative physical layer performance results from the past 24 hours. These are defined and accumulated per ANSI specification T1.403 and AT&T publication 54016. Depending upon the configured T1 Framing mode, these results may be retrieved via ESF facility data link by service personnel.

tfrapT1TotalEntry.name: tfrapT1TotalEntry
tfrapT1TotalEntry.description: An entry in the T1 Physical Layer Measurement Totals table.

tfrapT1TotalIndex.name: tfrapT1TotalIndex
tfrapT1TotalIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the t1 interface to which this entry is applica- ble. There is only one T1 port on this device so this index must be 1.

tfrapT1TotalESs.name: tfrapT1TotalESs
tfrapT1TotalESs.description: The number of Errored Seconds encountered by a t1 interface in the previous 24 hour interval. An errored second is a one-second interval with CRC errors or a loss of frame sync occurred.

tfrapT1TotalSESs.name: tfrapT1TotalSESs
tfrapT1TotalSESs.description: The number of Severely Errored Seconds encoun- tered by a t1 interface in the previous 24 hour interval. A severely errored second is a one second interval with more than 320 CRC errors or one or more frame sync losses.

tfrapT1TotalSEFSs.name: tfrapT1TotalSEFSs
tfrapT1TotalSEFSs.description: The number of Severely Errored Framing Seconds 24 hour interval. A SEFS is a one second interval with one or more frame sync losses.

tfrapT1TotalUASs.name: tfrapT1TotalUASs
tfrapT1TotalUASs.description: The number of Unavailable Seconds encountered by a t1 interface in the previous 24 hour in- terval. A UAS is a one second interval during which the received signal is classified as 'unavailable due to excessive errors'. A signal is unavailable after receiving ten consective severely errored seconds and stays unavailable until ten seconds without a severely errored second occur.

tfrapT1TotalCSSs.name: tfrapT1TotalCSSs
tfrapT1TotalCSSs.description: The number of Controlled Slip Seconds encoun- tered by a t1 interface in the previous 24 hour interval. A controlled slip is the replication or deletion of a T1 frame at the receiver. These events often indicate a T1 network timing problem.

tfrapT1TotalBESs.name: tfrapT1TotalBESs
tfrapT1TotalBESs.description: The number of Bursty Errored Seconds (BESs) encountered by a t1 interface in the previous 24 hour interval. A BES is a one second interval with more than one and less than 320 CRC errors.

tfrapT1TotalLCVs.name: tfrapT1TotalLCVs
tfrapT1TotalLCVs.description: The number of Line Code Violations (LCVs) en- countered by a t1 interface in the current 15 minute interval. LCVs are non-B8ZS related violations of the alternate mark inversion protocol. An excessive count usually indicates a B8ZS/AMI configuration mismatch in the T1 network.

tfrapT1PerfFreezeState.name: tfrapT1PerfFreezeState
tfrapT1PerfFreezeState.description: This command halts the node's performance monitoring and freezes the current, interval, and total performance register values.

tfrapT1PerfClearEvents.name: tfrapT1PerfClearEvents
tfrapT1PerfClearEvents.description: This command resets all of the (user's) error event registers. This includes the CRC6 and Out-of-Frame counts. It does not affect the interval or 24 hour performance totals.

tfrapT1PerfClearAll.name: tfrapT1PerfClearAll
tfrapT1PerfClearAll.description: This command resets all of the (user's) performance registers.

tfrapPerfMgmtIpIFInOctets.name: tfrapPerfMgmtIpIFInOctets
tfrapPerfMgmtIpIFInOctets.description: The count of all octets associated with received frames that are specifically addressed as management packets for this unit. Same as ifInOctets in mib-2.

tfrapPerfMgmtIpIFInErrors.name: tfrapPerfMgmtIpIFInErrors
tfrapPerfMgmtIpIFInErrors.description: The count of packets associated with received frames that are specifically addressed as management packets for this unit which could not be handled because of errors. Same as ifInErrors in mib-2.

tfrapPerfMgmtIpIFOutOctets.name: tfrapPerfMgmtIpIFOutOctets
tfrapPerfMgmtIpIFOutOctets.description: The count of all octets associated with generated frames that are specifically addressed as management packets from this unit. Same as ifOutOctets in mib-2. Same as ifOutOctets in mib-2.

tfrapPerfMgmtIpIFOperStatus.name: tfrapPerfMgmtIpIFOperStatus
tfrapPerfMgmtIpIFOperStatus.description: The current operational state of the management interface. Same as ifOperStatus in mib-2. (1) Interface Up (2) Interface Down (3) Interface in Test

tfrapPerfMgmtIpIPInRcv.name: tfrapPerfMgmtIpIPInRcv
tfrapPerfMgmtIpIPInRcv.description: The count of all ip datagrams received which are specifically addressed as management frames for this unit. Same as ipInReceives in mib-2.

tfrapPerfMgmtIpIPInHdrErr.name: tfrapPerfMgmtIpIPInHdrErr
tfrapPerfMgmtIpIPInHdrErr.description: The count of ip datagrams received which are specifically addressed as management frames for this unit that were discarded because of errors in their IP headers. Same as ipInHdrErrors in mib-2.

tfrapPerfMgmtIpIPInAddrErr.name: tfrapPerfMgmtIpIPInAddrErr
tfrapPerfMgmtIpIPInAddrErr.description: The count of ip datagrams received which are specifically addressed as management frames for this unit that were discarded because unexpected or invalid IP addresses in their IP headers. Same as ipInAddrErrors in mib-2.

tfrapPerfMgmtIpIPInProtUnk.name: tfrapPerfMgmtIpIPInProtUnk
tfrapPerfMgmtIpIPInProtUnk.description: The count of ip datagrams received which are specifically addressed as management frames for this unit that were discarded because of unsupported protocols. Same as ipInUnknownProtos in mib-2.

tfrapPerfMgmtIpIPInDscrd.name: tfrapPerfMgmtIpIPInDscrd
tfrapPerfMgmtIpIPInDscrd.description: The count of datagrams received which are specifically addressed as management frames for this unit that were discarded for reasons other than a problem with the datagram. Same as ipInDiscards in mib-2.

tfrapPerfMgmtIpIPInDlvrs.name: tfrapPerfMgmtIpIPInDlvrs
tfrapPerfMgmtIpIPInDlvrs.description: The count ofip datagrams received which are specifically addressed as management frames for this unit that were delivered to IP client protocols. Same as ipInDelivers in mib-2.

tfrapPerfMgmtIpIPOutRqst.name: tfrapPerfMgmtIpIPOutRqst
tfrapPerfMgmtIpIPOutRqst.description: The count of all outgoing datagrams generated by this unit which are specifically addressed as management frames. Same as ipOutRequests in mib-2.

tfrapPerfMgmtIpIPOutDscrd.name: tfrapPerfMgmtIpIPOutDscrd
tfrapPerfMgmtIpIPOutDscrd.description: The count of outgoing datagrams generated by this unit which are specifically addressed as management frames that were discarded for reasons other than a problem with the datagram. Same as ipOutDiscards in mib-2.

tfrapPerfMgmtIpIPOutNoRt.name: tfrapPerfMgmtIpIPOutNoRt
tfrapPerfMgmtIpIPOutNoRt.description: The count of outgoing datagrams generated by this unit which are specifically addressed as management frames that were discarded because no route could be found for transmission. Same as ipOutNoRoutes in mib-2.

tfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPInMsgs.name: tfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPInMsgs
tfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPInMsgs.description: The count of all ICMP messages received which are addressed to this unit. Same as icmpInMsgs in mib-2.

tfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPInErrors.name: tfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPInErrors
tfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPInErrors.description: The count of ICMP messages received which are addressed to this unit but contain errors. Same as icmpInErrors in mib-2.

tfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPInDestUnreachs.name: tfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPInDestUnreachs
tfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPInDestUnreachs.description: The count of ICMP Destination Unreachable messages received which are addressed to this unit. Same as icmpInDestUnreachs in mib-2.

tfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPInTimeExcds.name: tfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPInTimeExcds
tfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPInTimeExcds.description: The count of ICMP Time Exceeded messages received which are addressed to this unit. Same as icmpInTimeExcds in mib-2.

tfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPInParmProbs.name: tfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPInParmProbs
tfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPInParmProbs.description: The count of ICMP Parameter Problem messages received which are addressed to this unit. Same as icmpInParmProbs in mib-2.

tfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPInRedirects.name: tfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPInRedirects
tfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPInRedirects.description: The count of ICMP Redirect messages received which are addressed to this unit. Same as icmpInRedirects in mib-2.

tfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPInEchos.name: tfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPInEchos
tfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPInEchos.description: The count of ICMP Echo messages received which are addressed to this unit. Same as icmpInEchos in mib-2.

tfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPInEchoReps.name: tfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPInEchoReps
tfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPInEchoReps.description: The count of ICMP Echo Reply messages received which are addressed to this unit. Same as icmpInEchoReps in mib-2.

tfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPOutMsgs.name: tfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPOutMsgs
tfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPOutMsgs.description: The count of all outgoing ICMP messages originating from this node. Same as icmpOutMsgs in mib-2.

tfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPOutErrors.name: tfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPOutErrors
tfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPOutErrors.description: The count of outgoing ICMP messages generated by this unit which are not transmitted due problems found by the ICMP layer. Same as icmpOutErrors in mib-2.

tfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPOutDestUnreachs.name: tfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPOutDestUnreachs
tfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPOutDestUnreachs.description: The count of outgoing ICMP Destination Unreachable messages generated by this unit. Same as icmpOutDestUnreachs in mib-2.

tfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPOutParmProbs.name: tfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPOutParmProbs
tfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPOutParmProbs.description: The count of outgoing ICMP Parameter Problem messages generated by this unit. Same as icmpOutParmProbs in mib-2.

tfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPOutRedirects.name: tfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPOutRedirects
tfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPOutRedirects.description: The count of outgoing ICMP Redirect messages generated by this unit. Same as icmpOutRedirects in mib-2.

tfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPOutEchos.name: tfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPOutEchos
tfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPOutEchos.description: The count of outgoing ICMP Echo messages generated by this unit. Same as icmpOutEchos in mib-2.

tfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPOutEchoReps.name: tfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPOutEchoReps
tfrapPerfMgmtIpICMPOutEchoReps.description: The count of outgoing ICMP Echo Reply messages generated by this unit. Same as icmpOutEchoReps in mib-2.

tfrapPerfMgmtIpUDPInDatagrams.name: tfrapPerfMgmtIpUDPInDatagrams
tfrapPerfMgmtIpUDPInDatagrams.description: The count of all UDP datagrams received that are addressed as management frames for this unit. Same as udpInDatagrams in mib-2.

tfrapPerfMgmtIpUDPOutDatagrams.name: tfrapPerfMgmtIpUDPOutDatagrams
tfrapPerfMgmtIpUDPOutDatagrams.description: The count of all UDP datagrams generated by this unit. Same as udpOutDatagrams in mib-2.

tfrapPerfMgmtIpUDPNoPorts.name: tfrapPerfMgmtIpUDPNoPorts
tfrapPerfMgmtIpUDPNoPorts.description: The count of all UDP datagrams received that are addressed as management frames for this unit with no application at the destination port. Same as udpNoPorts in mib-2.

tfrapPerfMgmtIpTCPActiveOpens.name: tfrapPerfMgmtIpTCPActiveOpens
tfrapPerfMgmtIpTCPActiveOpens.description: The count of the times TCP connections specific to this unit have made a direct state transition from CLOSED to SYN-SENT. Same as tcpActiveOpens in mib-2.

tfrapPerfMgmtIpTCPPassiveOpens.name: tfrapPerfMgmtIpTCPPassiveOpens
tfrapPerfMgmtIpTCPPassiveOpens.description: The count of the times TCP connections specific to this unit have made a direct state transition from CLOSED to SYN-RCVD. Same as tcpPassiveOpens in mib-2.

tfrapPerfMgmtIpTCPAttemptFails.name: tfrapPerfMgmtIpTCPAttemptFails
tfrapPerfMgmtIpTCPAttemptFails.description: The count of the times TCP connections specific to this unit have made a direct state transition from SYN-SENT or SYN-RCVD to CLOSED state, plus the count of the times TCP connections have made a direct state transition from SYN-RCVD to LISTEN. Same as tcpAttemptFails in mib-2.

tfrapPerfMgmtIpTCPCurrEstab.name: tfrapPerfMgmtIpTCPCurrEstab
tfrapPerfMgmtIpTCPCurrEstab.description: The count of the TCP connections specific to this unit in state ESTABLISHED or CLOSE-WAIT. Same as tcpCurrEstab in mib-2.

tfrapPerfMgmtIpTCPInSegs.name: tfrapPerfMgmtIpTCPInSegs
tfrapPerfMgmtIpTCPInSegs.description: The count of all the segments received that are addressed as management frames for this unit. Same as tcpInSegs in mib-2.

tfrapPerfMgmtIpTCPOutSegs.name: tfrapPerfMgmtIpTCPOutSegs
tfrapPerfMgmtIpTCPOutSegs.description: The count of all the segments generated from this unit. Same as tcpOutSegs in mib-2.

tfrapPerfThruputPerIntfTable.name: tfrapPerfThruputPerIntfTable
tfrapPerfThruputPerIntfTable.description: The throughput per interface table. These values are accumulated across all DLCIs.

tfrapPerfThruputPerIntfEntry.name: tfrapPerfThruputPerIntfEntry
tfrapPerfThruputPerIntfEntry.description: An entry in the throughput per interface table.

tfrapPerfThruputPerIntfIndex.name: tfrapPerfThruputPerIntfIndex
tfrapPerfThruputPerIntfIndex.description: Interface for which the statistics apply. (1) DTE interface (2) T1 interface

tfrapPerfThruputPerIntfRxByteCnt.name: tfrapPerfThruputPerIntfRxByteCnt
tfrapPerfThruputPerIntfRxByteCnt.description: The number of framed bytes that have been received on this interface.

tfrapPerfThruputPerIntfTxByteCnt.name: tfrapPerfThruputPerIntfTxByteCnt
tfrapPerfThruputPerIntfTxByteCnt.description: The number of framed bytes that have been transmit on this interface.

tfrapPerfThruputPerIntfRxFrameCnt.name: tfrapPerfThruputPerIntfRxFrameCnt
tfrapPerfThruputPerIntfRxFrameCnt.description: The number of frames that have been received on this interface.

tfrapPerfThruputPerIntfTxFrameCnt.name: tfrapPerfThruputPerIntfTxFrameCnt
tfrapPerfThruputPerIntfTxFrameCnt.description: The number of frames that have been transmit on this interface.

tfrapPerfThruputPerIntfRxCrcErrCnt.name: tfrapPerfThruputPerIntfRxCrcErrCnt
tfrapPerfThruputPerIntfRxCrcErrCnt.description: The number of frames with CRC errors received on this interface.

tfrapPerfThruputPerIntfRxAbortCnt.name: tfrapPerfThruputPerIntfRxAbortCnt
tfrapPerfThruputPerIntfRxAbortCnt.description: The number of aborted frames received on this interface.

tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciTable.name: tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciTable
tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciTable.description: Layer 2 statistics on a per-DLCI basis. Transmit direction is from DTE to WAN and receive direction is from the WAN towards the DTE.

tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciEntry.name: tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciEntry
tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciEntry.description: The Statistics for a particular Data Link Connection Management Interface (DLCI).

tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciIndex.name: tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciIndex
tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciIndex.description: This value must be in the range 1-3. Other than that, this value is ignored as all three will return the same result.

tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciValue.name: tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciValue
tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciValue.description: The DLCI value in which the Statistics are associated.

tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciCreateTime.name: tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciCreateTime
tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciCreateTime.description: The amount of time elapsed since this DLCI was first detected through traffic sensing or in an LMI message (in seconds).

tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciChangeTime.name: tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciChangeTime
tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciChangeTime.description: The amount of elapsed time since this DLCI last changed state from active to inactive or vice versa (in seconds).

tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciRxByte.name: tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciRxByte
tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciRxByte.description: The number of bytes that have been received from the WAN towards the DTE on this DLCI. This count will include any frames that are terminated by the unit and do not pass through to the opposite interface (management and networking data).

tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciTxByte.name: tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciTxByte
tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciTxByte.description: The number of bytes that have been transmit from the DTE towards the WAN on this DLCI. This count will include any frames that are terminated by the unit and do not pass through to the opposite interface (management and networking data).

tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciRxFrame.name: tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciRxFrame
tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciRxFrame.description: The number of frames that have been received from the WAN towards to the DTE on this DLCI. This count will include any frames that are terminated by the unit and do not pass through to the opposite interface (management and networking data).

tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciTxFrame.name: tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciTxFrame
tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciTxFrame.description: The number of frames that have been transmit from the DTE towards the WAN on this DLCI. This count will include any frames that are terminated by the unit and do not pass through to the opposite interface (management and networking data).

tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciRxFecn.name: tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciRxFecn
tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciRxFecn.description: The number frames received from the WAN towards the DTE that have had the Forward Explict Congestion Notification (FECN) bit set on this DLCI. This count will include any frames that are terminated by the unit and do not pass through to the opposite interface (management and networking data).

tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciRxBecn.name: tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciRxBecn
tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciRxBecn.description: The number frames received from the WAN towards the DTE that have had the Backward Explict Congestion Notification (BECN) bit set on this DLCI. This count will include any frames that are terminated by the unit and do not pass through to the opposite interface (management and networking data).

tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciRxDe.name: tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciRxDe
tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciRxDe.description: The number frames received from the WAN towards the DTE that have had the Discard Eligibility (DE) bit set on this DLCI. This count will include any frames that are terminated by the unit and do not pass through to the opposite interface (management and networking data).

tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciTxDe.name: tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciTxDe
tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciTxDe.description: The number frames transmit towards the WAN from the DTE that have had the Discard Eligibility (DE) bit set on this DLCI. This count will include any frames that are terminated by the unit and do not pass through to the opposite interface (management and networking data).

tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciRxThruput.name: tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciRxThruput
tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciRxThruput.description: The number of bits/sec received from the WAN on this DLCI. This count will include any frames that are terminated by the unit and do not pass through to the opposite interface (management and networking data).

tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciTxThruput.name: tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciTxThruput
tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciTxThruput.description: The number of bits/sec transmit to the WAN on this DLCI. This count will include any frames that are terminated by the unit and do not pass through to the opposite interface (management and networking data).

tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciCIR.name: tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciCIR
tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciCIR.description: The Committed Information Rate (CIR) for this DLCI. This can come form one of three sources: From the LMI Full Status Response, configured by the user, or the DTE line rate (default).

tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciCirType.name: tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciCirType
tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciCirType.description: The source of the CIR value for this DLCI. (1) CIR acquired from LMI message. Will override user configured CIR. This feature is not supported by all Frame Relay DCE (switches). (2) CIR configured by user. (3) CIR is DTE Line Rate. Default if CIR is not set by one of the other methods.

tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciUptime.name: tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciUptime
tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciUptime.description: The total amount of time that the DLCI has been up as reproted by the LMI Full Status Response (in seconds).

tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciDowntime.name: tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciDowntime
tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciDowntime.description: The total amount of time that the DLCI has been declared down (in seconds). A DLCI is Down if it's explicitly declared Inactive through LMI or if it's missing from the LMI Full Status message or if there is no Full Status message at all.

tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciPvcState.name: tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciPvcState
tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciPvcState.description: The current state of the DLCI: (1) DLCI marked active in last full status LMI (2) DLCI in last full status LMI but not marked active (3) DLCI has never been seen in a full status LMI (4) DLCI was seen at least once in a full status LMI but was not in the last full status LMI (5) the full status LMI has timed out; all previously active or inactive DLCIs are changed to this state (6) DLCI was detected in the traffic stream and a full status LMI has not been received so the state cannot be determined yet.

tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciOutageCount.name: tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciOutageCount
tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciOutageCount.description: The number of times the smperPerfThruputPerDlciPvcState transitions from pvc-active or pvc-undetermined to one of the other (inactive) states.

tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciAvailability.name: tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciAvailability
tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciAvailability.description: The measure of the percentage time the DLCI is available: UpTime/CreateTime or zero if CreateTime = 0. (in 1/1000 per cent; i.e. availability = 1000 converts to 1%).

tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciMTBSO.name: tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciMTBSO
tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciMTBSO.description: Mean Time Between Service Outages: UpTime/OutageCount or zero if OutageCount = 0 (in seconds).

tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciMTTSR.name: tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciMTTSR
tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciMTTSR.description: Mean Time to ServiceRestoral: DownTime/OutageCount or zero if OutageCount = 0 (in seconds).

tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciEncapType.name: tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciEncapType
tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciEncapType.description: The encapsulation protocol seen in the last frame analyzed on this DLCI: (1) DLCI is the LMI DLCI or no frames have been analyzed (2) The encapsulation is per rfc1490 (3) The encapsulation is per Cisco proprietary (4) The encapsulation is per Annex-G (X.25 over frame relay) (5) The encapsulation is not one of the above.

tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciRxUtilizationStat.name: tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciRxUtilizationStatus
tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciRxUtilizationStat.description: The status of the per-DLCI utilization alarm in the receive direction. (1) there is no alarm condition; utilization is under the configured CIR percentage threshold; if traps are enabled and the alarm had been previously triggered, a utilization alarm clear trap will be sent. (2) the utilization has been over the configured CIR percentage threshold for less than the configured duration. (3) the utilization has been over the configured CIR percentage threshold for more than the configured duration; if traps are enabled a utilization exceeded trap will be sent. (4) the utilization has been under the configured CIR percentage threshold for less than the configured duration.

tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciTxUtilizationStat.name: tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciTxUtilizationStatus
tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciTxUtilizationStat.description: The status of the per-DLCI utilization alarm in the transmit direction. (1) there is no alarm condition; utilization is under the configured CIR percentage threshold; if traps are enabled and the alarm had been previously triggered, a utilization alarm clear trap will be sent. (2) the utilization has been over the configured CIR percentage threshold for less than the configured duration. (3) the utilization has been over the configured CIR percentage threshold for more than the configured duration; if traps are enabled a utilization exceeded trap will be sent. (4) the utilization has been under the configured CIR percentage threshold for less than the configured duration.

tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciEIR.name: tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciEIR
tfrapPerfThruputPerDlciEIR.description: The Excess Information Rate. This is defined to be the maximum rate traffic is (supposed to be) allowed to burst to.

tfrapPerfThruputCmdClearDteStats.name: tfrapPerfThruputCmdClearDteStats
tfrapPerfThruputCmdClearDteStats.description: Allows the user to zero out all the interface statistics in the DTE portion of the ThruputPerIntf statistics table. (1) Clear DTE interface statistics command.

tfrapPerfThruputCmdClearT1Stats.name: tfrapPerfThruputCmdClearT1Stats
tfrapPerfThruputCmdClearT1Stats.description: Allows the user to zero out all the interface statistics in the WAN portion of the ThruputPerIntf statistics table. (1) Clear WAN interface statistics command.

tfrapPerfThruputCmdClearAllIntfStats.name: tfrapPerfThruputCmdClearAllIntfStats
tfrapPerfThruputCmdClearAllIntfStats.description: Allows the user to zero out all the statistics in the ThruputPerIntf statistics table.

tfrapPerfThruputCmdClearDlciStats.name: tfrapPerfThruputCmdClearDlciStats
tfrapPerfThruputCmdClearDlciStats.description: Allows the user to zero out all the per-DLCI statistics in the ThruputPerDlci statistics table and the the short term statistics tables. (1) Clear layer 2 per-DLCI statistics command.

tfrapPerfThruputCmdClearAllStats.name: tfrapPerfThruputCmdClearAllStats
tfrapPerfThruputCmdClearAllStats.description: Allows the user to zero out all the statistics in the ThruputPerIntf and ThruputPerDlci statistics tables and in the short term statistics tables. (1) Clear all interface and layer 2 per-DLCI statistics.

tfrapPerfThruputCmdRemoveStsDlci.name: tfrapPerfThruputCmdRemoveStsDlci
tfrapPerfThruputCmdRemoveStsDlci.description: Allows the user to remove a Dlci from the short term statistics tables.

tfrapPerfThruputCmdReplaceDlciTable.name: tfrapPerfThruputCmdReplaceDlciTable
tfrapPerfThruputCmdReplaceDlciTable.description: Allows the user to replace one DLCI in the short-term statistics table with another one.

tfrapPerfThruputCmdReplaceDlciEntry.name: tfrapPerfThruputCmdReplaceDlciEntry
tfrapPerfThruputCmdReplaceDlciEntry.description: Allows the user to replace one DLCI in the short-term statistics table with another one.

tfrapPerfThruputCmdReplaceDlciValue.name: tfrapPerfThruputCmdReplaceDlciValue
tfrapPerfThruputCmdReplaceDlciValue.description: A Dlci that is in the short-term stats table. Index by this Dlci value to identify the statistics entry to be replaced.

tfrapPerfThruputCmdReplaceDlciNewValue.name: tfrapPerfThruputCmdReplaceDlciNewValue
tfrapPerfThruputCmdReplaceDlciNewValue.description: A Dlci that is to replace another in the short-term stats table. Index by this Dlci value to identify the statistics entry to do the replacing.

tfrapPerfThruputCmdAvailabilityStsDlciRe.name: tfrapPerfThruputCmdAvailabilityStsDlciReset
tfrapPerfThruputCmdAvailabilityStsDlciRe.description: Allows the user to reset the availability statistics of an individual Dlci within the short-term stats table.

tfrapPerfThruputCmdAvailabilityStsDlciRe.name: tfrapPerfThruputCmdAvailabilityStsDlciResetAll
tfrapPerfThruputCmdAvailabilityStsDlciRe.description: Allows the user to reset the availability statistics of all Dlci's within the short-term stats table.

tfrapPerfThruputCmdCountsStsDlciReset.name: tfrapPerfThruputCmdCountsStsDlciReset
tfrapPerfThruputCmdCountsStsDlciReset.description: Allows the user to reset the count statistics of an individual Dlci within the short-term stats table.

tfrapPerfThruputCmdCountsStsDlciResetAll.name: tfrapPerfThruputCmdCountsStsDlciResetAll
tfrapPerfThruputCmdCountsStsDlciResetAll.description: Allows the user to reset the count statistics of all Dlci's within the short-term stats table.

tfrapPerfThruputCmdAllStsDlciReset.name: tfrapPerfThruputCmdAllStsDlciReset
tfrapPerfThruputCmdAllStsDlciReset.description: Allows the user to reset both the count and availability statistics of an individual Dlci within the short-term stats table.

tfrapPerfThruputCmdAllStsDlciResetAll.name: tfrapPerfThruputCmdAllStsDlciResetAll
tfrapPerfThruputCmdAllStsDlciResetAll.description: Allows the user to reset both the count and the availability statistics of all Dlci's within the short-term stats table.

tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTable.name: tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTable
tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTable.description: The Short Term Statistics on the Network Layer protocol for each DLCI. These are protocol-based per-DLCI statistics. The Short Term model maintains three intervals: current, previous, and cumulative totals. Interval duration is defined by the Short Term Timer (CfgFrPerfTimersSTInterval).

tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciEntry.name: tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciEntry
tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciEntry.description: The Network Layer Short Term Statistics for a particular DLCI. This table organizes statistics by high-layer network protocol.

tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciInterval.name: tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciInterval
tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciInterval.description: The Short Term statistics model maintains three intervals: current, previous, and cumulative totals. Interval duration is defined by the Short Term Timer (CfgFrPerfTimersSTInterval). (1) Currently active short term interval (2) Previously completed short term interval (3) Cumulative total since last cleared.

tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciValue.name: tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciValue
tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciValue.description: The DLCI value with which the Statistics are associated.

tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxTotal.name: tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxTotal
tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxTotal.description: The total number of received Network Layer bytes that have been counted on this DLCI.

tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxTotal.name: tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxTotal
tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxTotal.description: The total number of transmitted Network Layer bytes that have been counted on this DLCI.

tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxIp.name: tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxIp
tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxIp.description: The number of received IP bytes that have been counted on this DLCI.

tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxIp.name: tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxIp
tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxIp.description: The number of transmitted IP bytes that have been counted on this DLCI.

tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxIpx.name: tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxIpx
tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxIpx.description: The number of received IPX bytes that have been counted on this DLCI.

tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxIpx.name: tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxIpx
tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxIpx.description: The number of transmitted IPX bytes that have been counted on this DLCI.

tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxSna.name: tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxSna
tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxSna.description: The number of received SNA bytes that have been counted on this DLCI.

tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxSna.name: tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxSna
tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxSna.description: The number of transmitted SNA bytes that have been counted on this DLCI.

tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxArp.name: tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxArp
tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxArp.description: The number of received ARP bytes that have been counted on this DLCI.

tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxArp.name: tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxArp
tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxArp.description: The number of transmitted ARP bytes that have been counted on this DLCI.

tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxCisco.name: tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxCisco
tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxCisco.description: The number of received Cisco protocol bytes that have been counted on this DLCI.

tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxCisco.name: tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxCisco
tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxCisco.description: The number of transmitted Cisco protocol bytes that have been counted on this DLCI.

tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxOther.name: tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxOther
tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxOther.description: The number of received bytes on this DLCI from protocols that are not counted elsewhere in this table.

tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxOther.name: tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxOther
tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxOther.description: The number of transmitted bytes on this DLCI from protocols that are not counted elsewhere in this table.

tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxVnip.name: tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxVnip
tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxVnip.description: The number of received VNIP protocol bytes that have been counted on this DLCI.

tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxVnip.name: tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxVnip
tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxVnip.description: The number of transmitted VNIP protocol bytes that have been counted on this DLCI.

tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxAnnexG.name: tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxAnnexG
tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciRxAnnexG.description: The number of received Annex G protocol bytes that have been counted on this DLCI.

tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxAnnexG.name: tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxAnnexG
tfrapPerfNetwProtoPerDlciTxAnnexG.description: The number of transmitted Annex G protocol bytes that have been counted on this DLCI.

tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalTable.name: tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalTable
tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalTable.description: The Short Term Statistics on Network Layer protocols summed across all DLCIs.

tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalEntry.name: tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalEntry
tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalEntry.description: The Network Layer Short Term Statistics for a particular DLCI.

tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalInterval.name: tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalInterval
tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalInterval.description: The Short Term statistics model maintains three intervals: current, previous, and cumulative totals. Interval duration is defined by the Short Term Timer (CfgFrPerfTimersSTInterval). (1) Currently active short term interval (2) Previously completed short term interval (3) Cumulative total since last cleared.

tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalRxTotal.name: tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalRxTotal
tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalRxTotal.description: The total number of received Network Layer bytes that have been counted across all DLCIs.

tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalTxTotal.name: tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalTxTotal
tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalTxTotal.description: The total number of transmitted Network Layer bytes that have been counted across all DLCIs.

tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalRxIp.name: tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalRxIp
tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalRxIp.description: The number of received IP bytes that have been counted across all DLCIs.

tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalTxIp.name: tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalTxIp
tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalTxIp.description: The number of transmitted IP bytes that have been counted across all DLCIs.

tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalRxIpx.name: tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalRxIpx
tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalRxIpx.description: The number of received IPX bytes that have been counted across all DLCIs.

tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalTxIpx.name: tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalTxIpx
tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalTxIpx.description: The number of transmitted IPX bytes that have been counted across all DLCIs.

tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalRxSna.name: tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalRxSna
tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalRxSna.description: The number of received SNA bytes that have been counted across all DLCIs.

tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalTxSna.name: tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalTxSna
tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalTxSna.description: The number of transmitted SNA bytes that have been counted across all DLCIs.

tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalRxArp.name: tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalRxArp
tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalRxArp.description: The number of received ARP bytes that have been counted across all DLCIs.

tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalTxArp.name: tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalTxArp
tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalTxArp.description: The number of transmitted ARP bytes that have been counted across all DLCIs.

tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalRxCisco.name: tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalRxCisco
tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalRxCisco.description: The number of received Cisco protocol bytes that have been counted across all DLCIs.

tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalTxCisco.name: tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalTxCisco
tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalTxCisco.description: The number of transmitted Cisco protocol bytes that have been counted across all DLCIs.

tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalRxOther.name: tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalRxOther
tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalRxOther.description: The number of received bytes across all DLCIs from protocols that are not counted elsewhere in this table.

tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalTxOther.name: tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalTxOther
tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalTxOther.description: The number of transmitted bytes across all DLCIs from protocols that are not counted elsewhere in this table.

tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalRxVnip.name: tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalRxVnip
tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalRxVnip.description: The number of received VNIP protocol bytes that have been counted across all DLCIs.

tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalTxVnip.name: tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalTxVnip
tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalTxVnip.description: The number of transmitted VNIP protocol bytes that have been counted across all DLCIs.

tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalRxAnnexG.name: tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalRxAnnexG
tfrapPerfNetwProtoTotalRxAnnexG.description: The number of received Annex G protocol bytes that have been counted across all DLCIs.

tfrapt1netwyellowalarmclear.description: Unit is no longer receiving a yellow alarm indication from the wide area network. Yellow alarm implies that the attached device is in a red alarm conditon. Red alarm is declared due to the extended absence of a properly framed signal.
